	 <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>104 threads, <a href=/quest.html?quest=178&start=0>1</a> <a href=/quest.html?quest=178&start=25>2</a> <a href=/quest.html?quest=178&start=50>3</a> <a href=/quest.html?quest=178&start=75>4</a> <a href=/quest.html?quest=178&start=100>5</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=/quest.html?quest=178&start=50>Previous Page</a>  <a href=/quest.html?quest=178&start=100>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><ul><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96998418129488></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96998418129488><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=178&mid=96998418129488>A few thoughts</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 26th 12:03 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off, I want to say that I thought this quest was a pretty good quest, even though I failed a few times before I got the bow. When I finally combined the required materials and was standiing there holding my very own Trueshot Longbow, I was exhilerated. I didn't look at it like I had wasted several days of my EQ life failing on attempt after attempt. I looked at it from a Role Playing perspective. The first time I tried, I didn't think I would succede, but I tried it anyway. And failed. Then I tried several more times and failed. So, I figured I my bowyering wasn't up to the task. So I shoved off and went to making arrows and arrows and arrows blah blah until I felt it was ok to give it another shot. When I was about to try to make the Trueshot, I asked the people in my guild to send up a prayer to their deity for luck and it worked! When it did work, I wasn't thinking "about frikkin' time" rather I was thinking "YESSSSSSS!!!!!!" and now I have a Trueshot Longbow. I think it's pretty cool that they added the element of you having to know what you're doing to get this quest (tbe bowyering part). Shoot, paladins have to be good smithy's to get their quest armor. I think more quests should be like this. That would add another dimension to the secondary skills (as well as the new armors they've added to smithing).<br><br>Now, on a non-role playing note. My fletching skill was less than 140 when I failed the first time. Then I went and raised it to a little over 140 and failed a few more times. Then someone told me that he had heard that at a skill of 160 it was almost 100% success rate. So I went and got my skill up to 162 and succeded the first time.<br><br>Also, that fools name in West Freeport is not Windshots it is just Windshot. I say this because in the quest description is says not to be fooled by imitators, that this is the real one, so a correct spelling would be nice. :P   AND you have to be better than indifferent to him. I went up to him indifferent and gave him the lantern and he said "Thank you. However, although you are not an enemy of Faydark's Champions, you still have yet to prove yourself to us." and I didn't get the treant wood. I had to head to Crushbone and raise my faction with Faydark's Champions. And, you have to give him a SMALL lantern, not a large one.<br><br>Nediam Nori<br>Ranger of 35 winters<br>Fennin Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
